social_posts.post_text: the artist formerly known as commedia jewelry got a MAJOR facelift // rebrand // Ozempic injection… so VERY stoked to share Annie Cavalero Jewelry 💖💎🌈💊🦄🍭✨ I figured if GP can juggle star turns in Hollywood classics like “Country Strong” while simultaneously slinging $1,249 gold-plated vibrators, I too can be More Than One Thing & use my name for writing, acting AND jewelry design (aka a triple threat who can’t sing or dance 💅🏻) So, if you’d like to treat a loved one such as yourself to some dopamine-drenched jewels & satisfy my insatiable need for attention // validate my existence + fragile sense of self-worth (or just want to see why I haven’t texted you back in the last 6 months… Y’ALL. Just when I thought I couldn’t possibly hate my phone more, I went ahead and decided teaching myself web & graphic design was a Good Idea 🫠) then wander on over to that link in bio + enter DOPE for 25% off everything 💊❤️‍🔥💊 FULLY aware the music has been playing me offstage for a while now, but to wrap up this little acceptance speech No One Asked For, hugest hugest thanks to: @apseyphoto for the GORGEOUS 💎 photography, guardian angel fairy godmother cheerleaders @whatsupkat @lisalisagee & @ktroseenriquez, unpaid intern // mødël husband @tonycavalero & all of YOU for the incredible support 💕 since launching this passion project as a little Etsy shop in 2020, over $9,200 from sales has been donated to a variety of nonprofits meaningful to us and I am so, so grateful ♥️

if you’ve ever met @ktroseenriquez, you know today is a national holiday because she was born 🥳 Katierose radiates joy. She is FUN personified. The energy changes when she walks into a room. When she looks at you, you feel seen. No one cheers harder for your wins, or is more capable of transforming the most mundane moments into the most memorable, or the worst days into beautiful ones. Of bringing the party, or sitting in silence, always somehow knowing exactly what the moment calls for and showing up 1,000%. She is magic. So for someone who gives so hard, heart wide open to lift up every single person who crosses her path - it is poignant and powerful that this was the year she stepped into her OWN light and shined SO HARD all over the entire WORLD with her brilliant, hilarious, vulnerable, unforgettable one woman show ✨ In the same amount of time it takes me to respond to approximately 1 text… she wrote, starred and internationally slayed in @queenoffishtown 🏆 I can’t wait to give a standing ovation to everything this next year has in store for this absolute QUEEN 💖 happiest happy birthday beautiful Katierose!!!! 🎉

Pure joy cheering on the real-life superheroes of @childrensla at the @makemarchmatter kick-off last week 💖 I’m so honored and thrilled to be a partner supporting their incredible work this month 🌈 20% of all March jewelry sales from my (brand new!!) online shop will be donated to the Artists Program @tonycavalero and I love so much (& under that 💎 #linkinbio there’s also a fundraiser button, if you’d like to donate to CHLA directly!) From 2014 on, Thursday was our favorite day of the week in Before Times, when we were lucky enough to be able to make art, play the bongos and rock out on the piano synthesizer in the Creative Oasis with the coolest, bravest kids and brilliant staff. Every week, we saw firsthand power of your support, and that is why we are such champions of this hospital, and the power of art and creativity. Expressive Arts Therapy is 100% philanthropically funded, and it cannot be overstated how meaningful their work is. #MAKEMARCHMATTER by donating, shopping the Creative Oasis’ Amazon Wish List, and supporting the many, many incredible businesses rallying around this beautiful community throughout the month if you’re able to ✨

so many incredible businesses are uniting in support of @childrensla for @makemarchmatter (I am especially obsessed with @shopesqueleto @cvtsoftserve + @amandakloots 💖) view all of the partners + upcoming events in support of this campaign at MakeMarchMatter.org 💕 I’m so honored to be a small part of this community, and excited to fundraise for the Expressive Arts therapy I’ve believed in for so long, with 20% of sales from my little online shop this month going to the Artists Program @tonycavalero and I have been volunteering with since my Baria, pre-Mrs. days ♥️

@tonycavalero Appreciation Post 🏆 while I have been laid up from surgery this week (even my body’s timing is impeccable 💅🏻🙃🫠) this man has been trekking down to the jewelry district, fighting my battles for designs that were promised to be finished weeks ago, Every. Single. Day. He literally got me home, medicated, and ventured right back out into traffic all the way downtown, where he has spent the majority of his waking hours since, chasing down as much as humanly possible in time for @shopesqueleto’s @makemarchmatter @childrensla benefit THIS SATURDAY!! We would love love love to see you there. Please come, shop for a cause we care so deeply about, and help me tell him what a good job he did. Thank you, Tony ♥️ you’re absolutely CRUSHING your unpaid jewelry internship (and the husband game, too)🕺🏼

TODAY ✨ come see us at @shopesqueleto from 3-6pm and support @makemarchmatter + @childrensla 🦋 So many fun 💎 including a few brand new designs (like these Tahoe babies  @tonycavalero braved Friday afternoon traffic to pick up downtown 🌊💙) There will be sips, snacks and so much gorgeous jewelry at this beautiful shop we love so much (they’re donating 10% of sales from their exquisite Los Feliz location all March long - if you can’t make it today, go see all of their incredible designers another time this month!!) And as always, you can donate to #chla and #makemarchmatter through the link in my bio!

HUGEST CONGRATS to the Cold Wallet dream team going straight #tothemoon 🤑 #HODL when this one comes out, babies 💸  So, SO proud of you @tonycavalero, and can only hope to make you as happy one day as working with all of these brilliant folks did 🤍 Was absolutely REKT when Tony first told me about this project, it was so good ⚡️ so I am going ALL IN & taking a bullish Maximalist position 💲 Cannot WAIT for this one to come out, congrats y’all 🚀 (Now pls advise in Comments on any missed opportunities for cringe here because I am OBSESSED with crypto lingo & comprehend 0%  of it 💰 the extent of my Bitcoin knowledge comes exclusively from my brother trying to explain the financial structure to me, Tony’s prep work for this shoot & the Twitter account of a guy I knew back in the day who has nothing to do with this movie but whose posts as of late are existentially terrifying & chill me to my core ✨)

last day to MAKE MARCH MATTER 🤍 @tonycavalero + I have tried to check @childrensla @makemarchmatter website anytime we needed // wanted anything this month - almost everything we would’ve spent money on anyway gave back to this incredible hospital, and supported the small businesses that give this sprawling city a soul. If you’re planning to order takeout tonight (@delilah @homestate @theniceguyla @pizzana @portosbakery @elcholo1923 @shakeshack), or coffee this weekend (@alfred), or burn off the week in a workout class (@amandakloots), or join me in eating our collective feelings with some frozen dopamine in the form of 🍦 (@cvtsoftserve) or *actual heaven* in 🍪 form (@milkjarcookies), or treat yourself to LA’s most gorgeous flowers (@flowertruckla), or something special you’ve been saving up for (@shopesqueleto @late.clothingla @loveshackfancy @my_hand_in_yours)… OR you even just need to tank up after spending most of your waking hours in traffic this week 🙃 (@chevron)… visit MakeMarchMatter.org first to see how those dollars can do some good (@tonycavalero + I both cried when we heard how much @officialpandaexpress had donated so far and will only be eating there every time we drive up the 5 to see my folks in NorCal, from here on out) ✨ I got really lucky with the cards I was dealt in this life, so honestly I often struggle with how and what to share on here. But if you’re in the market for some 💎 I’m donating 20% of sales this month to CHLA’s Artists Program, where Tony and I have been badged volunteers since my name was still Annie Baria ♥️ The brilliant woman who runs this program doesn’t have an account I can tag (which in & of itself is indicative of her character)… BUT I think the fact that she dyes her hair like a 🌈 to make kids smile when she walks into a room speaks volumes to her heart, and the care, creativity, and tireless, awe-inspiring work of her entire team that @tonycavalero + I are so, so honored to be on the sidelines cheering for 💖 #makemarchmatter

if you operate on the same plane of the space-time continuum as I do & would still like to #MakeMarchMatter for @childrensla even though it is now April… there are some new 💎 in the shop + I am still adding up all the numbers, so we’ll donate 20% of any sales from today, too ♥️💕♥️ thank you so much for all the support this @makemarchmatter month, it means the world to me. Promise to go back to regularly scheduled programming soon, since I’m pretty sure the algorithm considers this an official @tonycavalero stan account 💖

Staged this little photo op Easter 2014, when I was trying to convince @tonycavalero to let me keep the dog I had accidentally adopted while he was in Vegas at a bachelor party (didn’t work, still took another month+ before he resigned himself to the fact that Maggie was his actual real life biological daughter 💖) #praisebe #eastermagic

We are so hugely grateful for your support of @childrensla @makemarchmatter 🌈🦋💖 between your generous donations to @tonycavalero + my fundraiser here on Instagram, and your jewelry purchases throughout March + @shopesqueleto trunk show, we raised a total of over $2,700 for our beloved Artists Program, where we have been badged volunteers longer than we have been married ♥️ thank you so (so SO) much!!

Our beautiful friend @shayan.asgharnia gave us THE GREATEST gift in clearing space in his busy schedule when he found out our Maggie girl was sick, capturing these gorgeous photos in advance of her grueling 5 weeks of treatment that started Monday 🙏🏻 His art is a reflection of his spirit, and we’re feeling so lucky and beyond grateful for these incredible images of our beauty queen baby 🤍 She has had a brutal few weeks, with what started as a (at the time, cute and seemingly innocuous) little head tilt that deteriorated so rapidly it felt like whiplash. In a matter of days, she went from running and playing to unable to walk or - on the day our vet sent us to the animal hospital - barely even lift her head. She was diagnosed with a brain tumor, and was so sick we thought we were going to lose her that day. She’s only 9, and it all happened so fast it was just horrifying. These dogs are our babies and I have been a complete wreck, but her team at VCA West has worked enough miracles already that our sweetest goofy girl was able to actually walk into her first radiation appointment 🤍 (Tippi, on the other hand, will outlive us all… Shayan got that wild woman to sit still long enough to capture her personality, too 🫶🏻 And @lherethere + @themurrrman won the lottery that we were babysitting Timber when Shayan came over to share his magic ✨) @tonycavalero and I love you Shayan, thank you so so much ♥️

social_posts.post_text: @tonycavalero leaving his 30’s behind like 💫 HAPPY BIRTHDAY my love. You charge into every single day with this amount of enthusiasm and optimism and joy, and I don’t know how you do it, but I am so grateful. Thank you for always looking for the good, and finding the light, and making the absolute most of every second we’re lucky enough to get. There hasn’t been a dull moment since the day I met you, and I can’t wait to see what this next decade brings 🤍

this goddess @hilarieburton radiates magic, and so does her gorgeous new book 💫 a meditation on finding as much meaning in the small moments as in the big; illuminating the enchantment and wonder and goodness in the everyday; and crafting a legacy from the experiences, ideas, feelings, and lens we view this messy, wonderful, heartbreaking, beautiful world through - by committing it all to paper. It’s as much of a gift to sit with her words, in all their wisdom and joy, as it is to sit with her in life. (I also can promise you it is *much* less heavy handed than this post, but I just really love her ok??) Hilarie walks through this world lifting up everyone lucky enough to be in her orbit, and - like her - this book is such a warm, inspiring, empowering guide to seeking out and celebrating the magic, mischief and mysticism in our own lives 🤍
